{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id796b1b76-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1826b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1826b"},"text":"§ 1826b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Duration of denial of port privileges and sanctions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any denial of port privileges or sanction under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1826a"},"text":"section 1826a of this title","children":[],"tail":" with respect to a nation shall remain in effect until such time as the Secretary of Commerce certifies to the President and the Congress that such nation has terminated large-scale driftnet fishing by its nationals and vessels beyond the exclusive economic zone of any nation or effectively addressed the offending activities for which the nation received a negative certification under 1826j(d) "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002678"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002678"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be preceded by “section”."}],"tail":" or 1826k(c) of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id796b1b77-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/582/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–582, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4903"},"text":"106 Stat. 4903","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/479/tIV/s403/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–479, title IV, § 403(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-01-12"},"text":"Jan. 12, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/3632"},"text":"120 Stat. 3632","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/81/tI/s102/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–81, title I, § 102(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/656"},"text":"129 Stat. 656","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id796b1b78-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id796b1b79-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id796b1b7a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the High Seas Driftnet Fisheries Enforcement Act, and not as part of the Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id796b1b7b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/81"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–81","children":[],"tail":" struck out “or illegal, unreported, or unregulated fishing” after “driftnet fishing” and inserted “or effectively addressed the offending activities for which the nation received a negative certification under 1826j(d) or 1826j(c) of this title” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2007—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/479"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–479","children":[],"tail":" inserted “or illegal, unreported, or unregulated fishing” after “driftnet fishing”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
